<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-357-502  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 357 502.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  June 1989 v38 n6 p914(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>t-TDA-diagnosable systems. (testable diagnosis array )</TITLE><AUTHOR>Chu, S.-C.; Armstrong, J.R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A simple hardware device, the testable diagnosis array (TDA) oflogic cells, is proposed to perform system-level fault diagnosison an identified class of t-TDA-diagnosable distributed systems.andO;The fault diagnosis algorithm is based on the Preparata, Metze,and Chien (PMC) model.andP;  The nature of t-TDA-diagnosabledistributed systems is extensively described.andP;  The functioning ofthe TDA is predicated on the existence of reliable components toexecute the PMC algorithm and that execution is bounded inpolynomial time.andP;  A testing graph is used to represent thedistribution of diagnostic information and map the data to a TDAstate with respect to a defined clock period.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Failure AnalysisSystems AnalysisDistributed SystemsFault ToleranceConnectivityLogic CircuitrySymmetrical.andO;Feature:   illustrationcharttable.andO;Caption:   A typical TDA. (chart)Out values for any combination of a, b, and in. (table)4-TDA-diagnosable system. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>